11/09/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Police arrested on Wednesday (September 10th) six high-ranking customs officials suspected of links to organised crime. 
Allegations against them include bribery, misuse of official positions and criminal affiliations. 
Authorities released no further information to protect the ongoing investigation. 
Police, however, did not exclude the possibility of further arrests. 
(Koha ditore, Express, Lajm, Telegrafi - 11/09/08)
